.TH "MediaList" "JS" "December 21, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
MediaList \- MediaList
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]MediaList\f[B]\f[R] interface represents the media
queries of a stylesheet, e.g.\ those set using a \f[CR]<link>\f[R]
element\[cq]s \f[CR]media\f[R] attribute.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] \f[CR]MediaList\f[R] is a live list; updating the list
using properties or methods listed below will immediately update the
behavior of the document.
.RE
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]MediaList.mediaText\f[R]
A stringifier that returns a string representing the
\f[CR]MediaList\f[R] as text, and also allows you to set a new
\f[CR]MediaList\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]MediaList.length\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the number of media queries in the \f[CR]MediaList\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]MediaList.appendMedium()\f[R]
Adds a media query to the \f[CR]MediaList\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]MediaList.deleteMedium()\f[R]
Removes a media query from the \f[CR]MediaList\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]MediaList.item()\f[R]
A getter that returns a string representing a media query as text, given
the media query\[cq]s index value inside the \f[CR]MediaList\f[R].
This method can also be called using the bracket (\f[CR][]\f[R]) syntax.
.TP
\f[B]MediaList.toString()\f[R]
Returns a string representation of this media list in the same format as
the object\[cq]s \f[CR]MediaList.mediaText\f[R] property.
.SH EXAMPLES
The following would log to the console a textual representation of the
\f[CR]MediaList\f[R] of the first stylesheet applied to the current
document.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] stylesheets = document.styleSheets;
\f[B]let\f[R] stylesheet = stylesheets[0];
console.log(stylesheet.media.mediaText);
.EE
